e office abroad, effective communication with international partners and customers becomes even more important. Therefore, many businesses have turned to international roaming services provided by major carriers to facilitate these interactions. Yet, the high usage costs associated with international roaming have rendered this option unappealing, leading businesses to explore alternatives.</p><p>To offer a more cost-effective solution, Global Link Asia Consulting has undertaken extensive research and testing to develop a method that offers convenient international communication support for businesses</p><p>The following article will delve into the specifics of this solution, providing comprehensive information for our amazing service.</p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="an-overview-of-the-international-roaming-service" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">1.</span> <span class="heading_text">An overview of the international roaming service?</span></h2><h3 class="indexed"><span id="what-is-international-roaming" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">1.1.</span> <span class="heading_text">What is international roaming?</span></h3><p>International roaming service allows mobile subscribers to use their mobile phones in foreign countries and territories that have established international roaming agreements. For your business operations, this means acquiring a digital SIM card with a specific foreign country's number, such as (+65) for Singapore, (+61) for Australia, (+33) for France, and so on.Â </p><p>Here are some examples of international roaming you can use:</p><ul> <li>Singapore: (+65)</li> <li>Australia: (+61)</li> <li>French: (+33)</li> <li>Germany: (+61)</li> <li>America: (+1)</li> <li>Hong Kong (China): (+852)</li> <li>Malaysia: (+60)</li> <li>Japan: (+81)</li> <li>United Kingdom: (+44), etc.</li> </ul><p style="margin: 11.25pt 0in 0.0001pt; line-height: 150%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; text-align: center;"><span style="line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #4c5560; font-size: 10pt;"><img style="display: block; margin: 10px auto;" src="../../../images/hinh-anh-bai-viet/Cac-dich-vu-ho-tro/dang-ki-so-dien-thoai-nuoc-ngoai/Call-forwarding/roaming.jpg" alt="roaming service" width="80%" height="80%"></span></p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="is-roaming-service-ideal-for-your-business" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">2.</span> <span class="heading_text">Is roaming service ideal for your business?</span></h2><p>While this service provides convenience for businesses seeking communication abroad, it does come with certain drawbacks. Usually, maintaining to use of these services leads to higher operation costs, which most businesses will try to reduce in the long term. These disadvantages are:</p><ul> <li>You must register or purchase a SIM number for that country (If you have multiple partners in ten countries, you will have to buy and maintain 10 sim, each for a country where your partner operates)</li> <li>High international roaming charges lead to considerable expenses for users</li> </ul><p>As a result, businesses should carefully assess the suitability of roaming services for their communication needs in Vietnam and consider potential alternatives.</p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="call-forwarding-service-your-solution-to-international-business" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">3.</span> <span class="heading_text">Call Forwarding service - Your solution to international business</span></h2><h3 class="indexed"><span id="what-is-the-difference-between-roaming-services-and-our-call-forwarding-services" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">3.1.</span> <span class="heading_text">What is the difference between Roaming services and our Call Forwarding services?</span></h3><p>With Call Forwarding, businesses can register phone numbers from over 60 major countries, including Singapore, the USA, Australia, Hong Kong (China), Japan, France, Germany, Malaysia, and the UK.Â </p><p>This service allows businesses to transfer calls from their registered foreign numbers to a designated number in your country, simplifying communication between international partners and customers.</p><p>For instance, a company owner like Mr. Hai, operating in Singapore and Australia, can benefit from two dedicated company phone numbers:</p><ul> <li>2 company phone numbers for Singapore (+65) and Australia (+61).</li> <li>When partners or customers call these numbers, the calls will be redirected to Mr. Hai's subscriber number in Vietnam (+84).Â </li> </ul><p>This approach eliminates the need to <strong>maintain separate domestic SIM cards</strong> for each country and enhances the company's image and professionalism in the eyes of partners and customers.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 9.75pt; line-height: 150%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #4c5560;"><img style="display: block; margin: 10px auto;" src="../../../images/hinh-anh-bai-viet/Cac-dich-vu-ho-tro/dang-ki-so-dien-thoai-nuoc-ngoai/Call-forwarding/call-forwarding-countries.png" alt="example of coutries where offer our call forwarding service" width="80%" height="80%" loading="lazy"></span></span></p><p>Â </p><h3 class="indexed"><span id="what-benefits-can-you-get-from-our-call-forwarding-services" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">3.2.</span> <span class="heading_text">What benefits can you get from our call-forwarding services?</span></h3><p>n addition, the advantages that this service brings to your business are far superior to international roaming services:</p><ul> <li><strong>Cost-effectiveness</strong>: The annual payment structure for registering phone numbers is more convenient t